Mockito documentation to guide me through the process. I'm curious about the best practices for utilizing Mockito, and I'm hoping that exploring the documentation will help clarify how to set everything up properly. Let’s see what I can find in the repo!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_yzMs4sp91NHjzqGvVenfIvbN|fc_0ff1bf32696707ab016a3a822ccacc8196bb0255e7c83ea29d", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"mockito-core|MockMaker|ProxyMockMaker|mock-maker-inline|mock-maker-subclass|byte-buddy-agent|Graal\" tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core docs metadata -S", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4138, "output": 90, "cacheRead": 10752, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 14980, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782219305247, "responseId": "resp_0ff1bf32696707ab016a3a8229c9b4819687a7d0792996699f"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_yzMs4sp91NHjzqGvVenfIvbN|fc_0ff1bf32696707ab016a3a822ccacc8196bb0255e7c83ea29d", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:5:This is the best way to provide support for GraalVM Native Image as it makes an out-of-the-box experience for users (no additional work required) and allows you to continuously test and maintain the metadata as part of your project.\ndocs/CONTRIBUTING.md:59:* GraalVM Reachability Metadata in this repo only contains JSON files as described\ndocs/CONTRIBUTING.md:99:* `metadata-version`: Specifies the subdirectory where the GraalVM configuration files (e.g., `reflect-config.json`) reside.\ndocs/CONTRIBUTING.md:114:* `override`: Boolean. If `true`, excludes outdated builtin GraalVM metadata.\ndocs/CONTRIBUTING.md:247:If your library or framework is tested with GraalVM Native Image, consider adding it to [this list](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/metadata/library-and-framework-list.json).\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/settings.gradle:20:rootProject.name = 'org.mockito.mockito-core_tests'\ndocs/build-infra.md:25:wires the GraalVM native-build-tools plugin, the `javaTest`/`nativeTest` lanes,\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/gradle.properties:2:metadata.dir = org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/build.gradle:18:    testImplementation \"org.mockito:mockito-core:$libraryVersion\"\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/build.gradle:22:    testRuntimeOnly 'net.bytebuddy:byte-buddy-agent:1.12.22'\ndocs/functional-spec.md:3:This document describes what the **GraalVM Reachability Metadata Repository** does for its users, who those users are, and the requirements that the repository, its build infrastructure, and its automation (Forge) must meet. For the structural and implementation overview that organizes these behaviors into components, see §AR-repository-architecture.\ndocs/functional-spec.md:12:The repository hosts curated, versioned **GraalVM reachability metadata** for community JVM libraries and frameworks, plus the test harness, CI, and AI automation that keep the metadata correct and up to date.\ndocs/functional-spec.md:14:Reachability metadata describes reflection, JNI, resource access, serialization, and proxy use that GraalVM `native-image` cannot determine through static analysis. By centralizing this metadata, the repository allows libraries that are not yet self-contained for native compilation to \"just work\" with `native-image` when consumed via the GraalVM Gradle and Maven plugins.\ndocs/functional-spec.md:20:| **Application developer** using GraalVM Native Image | Build a native image of an application that depends on third-party libraries without writing reachability metadata by hand; check whether a given library is supported; request support for a missing library. | Consumes metadata indirectly — the GraalVM Gradle/Maven plugin downloads it from this repository at build time. Checks support via `curl … check-library-support.sh \\| bash -s \"<group>:<artifact>:<version>\"` or by browsing [the libraries-and-frameworks page](https://www.graalvm.org/native-image/libraries-and-frameworks/). Requests a new library by filing a [`01_support_new_library`](../.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/01_support_new_library.yml) issue, or updates an existing one via [`02_update_existing_library`](../.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/02_update_existing_library.yml). |\ndocs/functional-spec.md:44:- A directory hierarchy under `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/` containing JSON files in the format described by GraalVM's [Native Image Manual Configuration](https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/dynamic-features/Reflection/#manual-configuration) reference.\ndocs/functional-spec.md:77:The `create-snapshot-release` workflow refreshes a floating `SNAPSHOT` GitHub Release on the `SNAPSHOT` tag after `master` pushes when metadata changed since the previous `SNAPSHOT` tag, or since the latest numbered release when bootstrapping (§CI-create-snapshot-release). It packages the repository with version `SNAPSHOT`, replaces the previous snapshot release/tag, and provides a continuously updated snapshot-style metadata bundle between numbered releases without taking GitHub's Latest marker from the newest numbered release. The packaged artifacts are what the GraalVM Gradle/Maven plugins consume.\ndocs/functional-spec.md:183:**3. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/reachability-metadata.json`** — the only file the plugin loads at native-image time. Schema [reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json](../metadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json) (a vendored copy of the upstream GraalVM schema), with top-level keys `reflection`, `jni`, `resources`, `bundles`, `serialization`, and `foreignCalls`. Every entry's `condition` carries exactly one key, `typeReached`, so the plugin can rely on conditional registration; `typeReached` is the schema's only condition form. The legacy split-config layout (`reflect-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, …) is no longer present.\ndocs/functional-spec.md:219:- **Metadata-only bundles.** Metadata files contain only JSON entries described by GraalVM's manual-configuration reference. Native-image properties (`native-image.properties`) and other build-time tweaks are forbidden — by default every library is runtime-initialized.\ndocs/functional-spec.md:243:- **Compatibility budget.** `verify-new-library-version-compatibility` caps each scheduled run at a fixed library budget and at most 30 newer versions per library, expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, and creates one aggregated GitHub issue per failed `(library, version)` pair.\ndocs/functional-spec.md:250:- **Future-defaults lane.** `future-defaults-all` is run only against early-access / `latest` / `dev` GraalVM builds, both locally (via `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all`) and in scheduled CI lanes that explicitly opt in via `ci.json`'s `nativeImageModeJavaVersions`.\ndocs/functional-spec.md:282:- Weekly numbered release artifacts and floating `SNAPSHOT` release artifacts consumed by the GraalVM Gradle/Maven plugins.\ndocs/functional-spec.md:392:A matrix job expands every candidate library across the configured GraalVM\ndocs/ci.md:20:`ci.json` is the single source of truth for which GraalVM JDK versions and OS\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json:5:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.mockito.internal.creation.proxy.ProxyMockMaker\"\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json:15:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.mockito.internal.creation.proxy.ProxyMockMaker\"\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json:25:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.mockito.internal.creation.proxy.ProxyMockMaker\"\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json:35:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.mockito.internal.creation.proxy.ProxyMockMaker\"\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json:45:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.mockito.internal.creation.proxy.ProxyMockMaker\"\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json:263:      \"glob\" : \"mockito-extensions/org.mockito.plugins.MockMaker\"\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/resources/mockito-extensions/org.mockito.plugins.MockMaker:1:org.mockito.internal.creation.proxy.ProxyMockMaker\ndocs/grund.md:3:The GraalVM Reachability Metadata Repository exists so application developers\ndocs/grund.md:10:The project aims to keep community JVM libraries usable with GraalVM Native\ndocs/architecture.md:11:At its core the repository is a **distribution of additive GraalVM reachability\ndocs/metadata.md:3:[`metadata/`](../metadata) is the repository's product: the curated GraalVM\ndocs/DEVELOPING.md:15:- `JAVA_HOME` should be set to JDK 25 or later. GraalVM is recommended to match CI.\ndocs/DEVELOPING.md:210:These tasks use Native Image runtime metadata tracing. They require a GraalVM build that supports `-H:+MetadataTracingSupport`, `-XX:TraceMetadata`, and `-XX:TraceMetadataConditionPackages`.\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/dynamic-access-exhaust-report.json:17:  \"coordinate\": \"org.mockito:mockito-core:5.0.0\",\ndocs/support/index.html:6:    <title>GraalVM Reachability Metadata Support Checker</title>\ndocs/support/index.html:418:            <span class=\"brand-title\">GraalVM Reachability Metadata</span>\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/4.8.1/settings.gradle:20:rootProject.name = 'org.mockito.mockito-core_tests'\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/4.8.1/README.md:3:Mockito works in GraalVM when using the `org.mockito.internal.creation.proxy.ProxyMockMaker`, which uses JDK proxies\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/4.8.1/gradle.properties:2:metadata.dir=org.mockito/mockito-core/4.8.1\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/4.8.1/build.gradle:14:\ttestImplementation \"org.mockito:mockito-core:$libraryVersion\"\ntests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/4.8.1/src/test/resources/mockito-extensions/org.mockito.plugins.MockMaker:1:org.mockito.internal.creation.proxy.ProxyMockMaker\nmetadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json:4:  \"title\": \"JSON schema for the reachability metadata used by GraalVM Native Image\",\nmetadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json:328:      \"title\": \"JSON schema for the FFM API configuration used by GraalVM Native Image\",\nmetadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json:374:      \"title\": \"Type descriptors used by GraalVM Native Image metadata files\",\nmetadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json:436:      \"title\": \"Method descriptors used by GraalVM Native Image metadata files\",\nmetadata/schemas/metadata-library-index-schema-v2.1.0.json:143:          \"description\": \"Marks this artifact as intentionally not applicable to GraalVM Native Image metadata.\"\nmetadata/org.mockito/mockito-core/index.json:8:    \"source-code-url\": \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/mockito/mockito-core/$version$/mockito-core-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.mockito/mockito-core/index.json:11:    \"documentation-url\": \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/mockito/mockito-core/$version$/mockito-core-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/org.mockito/mockito-core/index.json:50:    \"source-code-url\": \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/mockito/mockito-core/$version$/mockito-core-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/com.datastax.oss/java-driver-shaded-guava/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"java-driver-shaded-guava packages Guava 25.1-jre under the com.datastax.oss.driver.shaded.guava namespace for use by the DataStax Java Driver for Apache Cassandra. The artifact avoids repeated shading across driver modules and includes GraalVM substitutions for Guava classes used when building native images.\",\nmetadata/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/reachability-metadata.json:1153:      \"type\" : \"org.mockito.internal.creation.bytebuddy.ByteBuddyMockMaker\",\nmetadata/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/reachability-metadata.json:1219:      \"type\" : \"org.mockito.internal.creation.proxy.ProxyMockMaker\",\nmetadata/org.mockito/mockito-core/4.8.1/reachability-metadata.json:158:      \"type\": \"org.mockito.internal.creation.proxy.ProxyMockMaker\",\nmetadata/org.mockito/mockito-core/4.8.1/reachability-metadata.json:208:      \"glob\": \"mockito-extensions/org.mockito.plugins.MockMaker\"\nmetadata/org.mockito/mockito-junit-jupiter/4.5.1/reachability-metadata.json:603:      \"type\" : \"org.mockito.internal.creation.bytebuddy.ByteBuddyMockMaker\",\nmetadata/org.mockito/mockito-junit-jupiter/4.5.1/reachability-metadata.json:814:          \"org.mockito.plugins.MockMaker\"\nmetadata/org.apache.kafka/kafka-streams/3.6.0/reachability-metadata.json:639:          \"org.mockito.plugins.MockMaker\"\nmetadata/org.apache.kafka/kafka-streams/3.6.0/reachability-metadata.json:647:      \"type\" : \"org.mockito.internal.creation.bytebuddy.ByteBuddyMockMaker\",\nmetadata/org.apache.kafka/kafka-streams/3.6.0/reachability-metadata.json:754:      \"glob\" : \"mockito-extensions/org.mockito.plugins.MockMaker\"\nmetadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-starter-test/index.json:5:    \"replacement\": \"Use class-bearing dependencies such as org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-test:2.7.18, org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-test-autoconfigure:2.7.18, org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter:5.8.2, org.mockito:mockito-core:4.5.1, and org.hamcrest:hamcrest:2.2.\"\nmetadata/com.github.ajalt.mordant/mordant-jvm-graal-ffi-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Mordant is a Kotlin multiplatform l